# 2. 謎が解けるとき

Tsukasa: Oh, Rui, it looks like we're the first ones here!
Rui: Yes. It's not quite the time we agreed upon yet, so let's...
Emu's Voice: Wheeeeeeee!!
Emu: Thanks for waiting, Tsukasa, Rui☆
Rui: Ah, Emu. Hello.
Tsukasa: Wait, wait, wait! What were you doing on top of that tree?!
Emu: Hehe♪ I was running a little late because of some class rep business, so I decided to take the short way!
Tsukasa: It looks pretty tall to me! Honestly...!
Tsukasa: Also, you didn't have to do that since Nene and her friend aren't here yet.
Rui: Hehe. To be fair, we are all ten minutes early.
Emu: Okay! Then, I'm glad I made it in time!
Emu: I can't wait to meet Nene's friend. I wonder what she's like!
Tsukasa: What was her name? Byakkomachi...? She's keen on learning more about Wonderlands×Showtime, so she must have an eye for talent!
Rui: She sounds like a very avid student.
Rui: She even asked to meet us at Phoenix Wonderland because she wants to learn as much as she can from the night show.
Emu: Hehe☆ I really hope she enjoys it!
Emu: Oh!
Nene: Thanks for waiting, you guys!
???: Hello. You must be Kusanagi's friends.
Byakkomachi: Nice to meet you all. My name is Suzu Byakkomachi, and I need to thank you for this wonderful opportunity.
Byakkomachi: Kusanagi's told me all about Wonderlands×Showtime. I've been hoping to meet you for quite a while now.
Emu: Oh...
Nene: Huh?
Emu: It's heeeeerrrrr!!!!
Byakkomachi: Wh-What...?
Byakkomachi: I see. You saw me leaving that meeting...
Emu: Yeah! I was really far away, but I saw someone with perfect posture!
Emu: That was you, right, Suzu?
Byakkomachi: Suzu...?
Nene: E-Emu, you shouldn't start calling her by her first name so suddenly...
Byakkomachi: No, that's okay. I was only a little surprised, since not many people do call me by it.
Byakkomachi: Please feel free to use whichever you prefer, Otori.
Emu: Thanks, Suzu!
Byakkomachi: Oh, sorry for getting us sidetracked. Where were we...?
Byakkomachi: I was definitely the person you saw that day, Otori, since I was scheduled to meet with the board then.
Byakkomachi: That being said...
Byakkomachi: I would greatly appreciate it if you could all keep this between us.
Byakkomachi: I'd like for everyone at the academy to treat me like any other actor or actress.
Nene: O-Okay, got it...!
Rui: Still, it's incredible to think that a student is being given an opportunity to be involved with how Morinomiya is run...
Byakkomachi: It is incredible. I'm very grateful to Grandfather for giving me this opportunity.
Nene: Grandfather?
Byakkomachi: Oh, he's the chairman of the board of the Morinomiya Revue.
Nene: What?
Emu & Tsukasa: The chairman?! Of the board?!
Rui: From what I understand, Morinomiya's chairman is quite the businessman...
Rui: I remember reading about how he became the chairman of the board after spending time as the president or one of the executives at several major companies...
Byakkomachi: That's right. When he was young, he apparently had a reputation for being a ruthless manager.
Byakkomachi: But he was actually a Morinomiya fan long before he ever became the board chair.
Byakkomachi: He even used to take me to see shows with him when I was little.
Emu: You went with your grandpa...
Byakkomachi: I've always loved how dazzling Morinomiya's shows are. I wanted to stand in the spotlight on that stage...
Byakkomachi: My family wanted me to enter the world of business, but then my grandfather said, “Why not try both...?”
Byakkomachi: Initially, all I did was sit in on some meetings. But I've been getting more and more opportunities lately to express my opinions regarding proposals, advertisements and such.
Tsukasa: Now that you mention it, I remember hearing about a recent ticket campaign running on Morinomiya's social media...
Byakkomachi: Oh, that was actually my idea. It was the result of us trying to get more young people to come see Morinomiya's shows.
Emu: That's...
Emu: That's amazing, Suzu!!!
Byakkomachi: Huh?
Emu: So, I'm also learning a lot about management and stuff right now!
Emu: My grandpa was the one who founded Phoenix Wonderland...
Emu: And I'm doing everything I can to make it a place that's filled with smiling guests!
Byakkomachi: Your grandfather...? You mentioned that your last name is Otori. Does that mean...?
Nene: Yeah, we also forget from time to time... Her family runs the Otori Group.
Byakkomachi: I had no idea. That explains why you're learning more about management...
Emu: Yup!
Emu: But my brothers are always telling me how my ideas aren't practical.
Emu: When Phoenix Wonderland was having trouble attracting guests, I couldn't come up with any good ideas to turn things around...
Emu: Which is why...
Emu: I think you're really amazing, Suzu! You're actually balancing your dreams with reality and making things work with everyone at Morinomiya!
Emu: I wanna be just like you! I want to learn to do what you do as fast as I possibly can!
Byakkomachi: Just like me...
Emu: Suzu...?
Byakkomachi: No, never mind...
Guest: Daddy! The night show's about to start!
Nene: Oh...
Rui: We've been chatting for quite a while now. Why don't we find a good place to watch the show?
Tsukasa: Yes, let's do that!
Byakkomachi: Let's go, Otori.
Emu: Oh, yeah...
Emu: (Just now...)
Emu: (Suzu seemed kinda sad for some reason...)
